The '''2013 South American Under-15 Football Championship''' (Spanish: Campeonato Sudamericano Sub-15 Bolivia 2013) is the 6th [[South American Under-15 Football Championship]] for national teams affiliated with [[CONMEBOL]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gol.com.bo/2013/02/el-campeonato-sudamericano-sub-15-sera.html |publisher=Futbol de Bolivia|title=El campeonato sudamericano sub 15 ser<U+00E1> en Bolivia |trans_title= The 2013 South American Under-15 Football Championship will be taken place in Bolivia |language=Spanish |date=6 February 2013 |accessdate=17 February 2013}}</ref> It is set to begin on November 16th, and end on November 30th. The winning team will represent South America in the [[Football at the 2014 Summer Youth Olympics|2014 Summer Youth Olympic Football Tournament]].<ref name=conmebol>{{cite web|last=CONMEBOL|title=Campeonato Sudamericano Sub-15 Bolivia 2013|url=http://conmebol.com/sites/default/files/sudamericano_sub_15_-_reglamento_del_torneo.pdf|accessdate=27 November 2013|language=Spanish}}</ref> 

